metadata.name: Contort #239
metadata.description:
Contort is the result of combining several previously meaningless experiments and learnings into a single cohesive algorithm. The project comes in a variety of shapes, bends, twists, colors, and other variations.  

The artwork builds towards the end-result by rendering a fixed number of forms per frame to ensure a smooth rendering process. Rendering times can vary depending on which features are combined by the hash.

metadata.name: Quantum Vacuum #539
metadata.description:
Empty space is not empty. It's filled with energy, transient fluctuations in quantum fields, bubbling with virtual particles popping in and out of existence. 

Part of an ongoing series of work combining my fascination with the fringes of fundamental physics, the emergence of complex behaviour through the interaction of very simple rules, and my obsession with hacking our perceptual systems. 

/Disclaimer: This is not a simulation, but an artistic conceptual interpretation and dramatization. :)

metadata.name: Beam #83
metadata.description:
Warning: GPU intensive!

Editions tiers:
- 125 free
- 125 1tz
- 125 2tz
- 125 3tz
(each tier will be unlocked upon the previous one's completion)

Realistic simulation of an emissive beam traversing a piece of glass of different color and density placed on a metallic surface

(the preview has a resolution factor of 0.75 so it's a bit blurry, the generator has a default of 0.9)

hold the left mouse button and drag to rotate the view around the center

hover with your mouse to spawn some settings controls:
- Resolution (performance-heavy)
- Light bounces
- Frame Samples
- Screenshot Button (takes a screenshot...if it doesn't download, you should open the generator in a new tab)
- Rendering toggle (once you are satisfied with the output you can pause the rendering)

Created with threejs + three-gpu-pathtracer

metadata.name: Angular Variations (Holding Space) #147
metadata.description:
Angular Variations. Holding space for transitions. Once minted the lines maintain their design while the spaces between adjust to accommodate changes in canvas size.

There are no rarity attributes assigned to this artwork, its value is intended to be determined by viewer aesthetic alone.

This artwork was created using p5js.

metadata.name: Disjoint and Disoriented #144
metadata.description:
Disjoint and Disoriented is about the abstract structure formed by the equalities and oppositions of its parts.

It might require high processing power depending on its features. A good desktop or laptop is recommended.

There are three render options available as url parameters in live mode:
- size=XXXX (up to 5760 pixels)
- texture=0 (disable canvas texture for print)
- shader=1 (use the shader throughout the painting process, can be heavy)

Created with p5.js and GLSL
dmarchi and lunarean, 2022.

metadata.name: Circles #86
metadata.description:
“Circles” is a set of generative artwork make by sophisticatedly designed algorithm with surprising randomness. It explores different combinations of size, shape, color, arrangement, etc., trying to create different feeling about circles. 

I like circle because it’s a metaphor to the cycle of life, we start at one point and end at the same point. No matter the circle is big or small, thick or thin，colorful or dull, we experience it as a cycle.

Press the ’s’ key to save the image to your computer.

#This is the republish version of "Circle" as the old version contain a bug so I have to disable it. All holders have been refunded.

#For apology, the first 100 editions will be free for minting. And then there will be price increase every time when another 100 mints complete.

metadata.name: fornio #42
metadata.description:
Fornio is a place in Italy next to Fidenza :-)
Since I love Fidenza I wanted to honor that OG project by naming my project this way.

There are different shapes that can be rendered (circle, triangle, square).
With a mix of sine waves it generates some really great outputs
